narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Awesome class. I learned a ton about important writers and really enjoyed it. I wish the class hadn't been at 9 am, especially on Thursday mornings when I was still drunk sometimes, but overall it's a great introduction to Foscolo, Leopardi and Manzoni and I'd highly recommend both the course and Mattia.

I would recommend this course for sure! It might be one of my favorite courses at Yale. It's a small course, which allows you get to know the teacher well and really get comfortable with the material and speaking up in class. Although I was a bit hesitant about the three poets you study: Foscolo, Leopardi, and Manzoni, I have enjoyed reading all their works.
I would wholeheartedly recommend this course-- it's a great survey of Italian romanticism that goes in depth to the three great Romantic authors-- Foscolo, Leopardi, and Manzoni. Take it! It's great.
It depends how serious you are about Italian. If you care about literary history and Italian literature, this is the course for you.
